        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 6:25AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 624 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bonney, or near Angleton, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Lake Jackson, Alvin, Angleton, Hitchcock, southwestern
Manvel, Richwood, Danbury, Arcola, Iowa Colony, Holiday Lakes,
Bailey's Prairie, Liverpool, Bonney, southeastern Sienna, Juliff,
Chocolate Bayou, and Rosharon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
